  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter was prompted by the detailed account of Prof. John Pringle Nichol&apos;s illness and death that was sent by Elizabeth Pease Nichol to Wendell Phillips. William Lloyd Garrison pays tribute to John Pringle Nichol&apos;s noble qualities. Garrison discourses on six considerations &quot;which should serve to break the force of such a separation [of death], while allowing the heart full scope of its sorrow.&quot; Garrison would like to visit Great Britain but his plans are not definite. If he should come, Samuel May, Jr., might accompany him.</subfield>
  </datafield>
